Hi! I'm Ben Zimmer. Most days, I drink black coffee and build high performance software systems for AI applications. I most recently worked as a data scientist at [Prolego](https://prolego.com) and as a machine learning research specialist at [3M](https://3m.com) / [Solventum](https://solventum.com).

#### Skills

* **Research:** image processing, 3D mesh processing, machine learning (deep learning, generative models, sequence models, LLMs)
* **Languages:** Python, C++, R, Scala, Java, MATLAB / Octave, Rust
* **Libraries and frameworks:** NumPy, OpenCV, scikit-learn, PyTorch, TensorFlow, SpeechBrain, ONNX, transformers, llama-cpp-python
* **Other**: functional programming, Git, Linux system administration, AWS (EC2, S3, SageMaker), Docker, Scrum

#### Personal Software Projects

* **[secondary](https://github.com/bdzimmer/secondary)** - markup language and static site generator for creating [fictional universes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fictional_universe), writing, and publishing.
* **[orbits](https://github.com/bdzimmer/orbits)** - calculate the positions of the planets and plan constant acceleration flight paths between them. Built around a tiny, pure functional [vector math library](https://github.com/bdzimmer/orbits/blob/master/src/main/scala/bdzimmer/orbits/Vectors.scala).

